            <h1>Why these app founders took a break from Penn to focus on &#8216;Down to Chill&#8217;</h1>
            <div class="synopsis" tag=""> 
              Four University of Pennsylvania students took the year off to promote their mobile app. Michael Powell, Matt Wojcieszek, Adam Elkassas and Arjun Raj Jain all have taken the year off to launch Down to Chill. “Down to Chill, simply put, is a way to see when your friends are free and a way to choose which friends you want to hang out without having to text them first,” said Powell, 20, the company&#8217;s COO. Users can connect the app to their Facebook account and then set a time when they&#8217;re “down to chill.” Users are matched up based on proximity, availability and their use of hashtags (such as #lunch or #drinking). Currently, Down to Chill has around 2,000 users, Powell said.
            </div>
