            <div class="synopsis" tag=""> 
              Two friends have just used a new smart phone application, “Down to Chill,” to make plans together. Designed by DuBois native Adam Elkassas and a team of college students, the app  uses Facebook to connect friends who have free time and want to hang out. “Down to Chill” can be downloaded for free through the App Store and can bring friends together at the swipe of a finger.
